:: Pretend everything is fine [en] {"position":"975,350","size":"100,100"}
“I don’t know… don’t you feel something’s off here?” I whispered.

Samuel raised an eyebrow. “Where exactly?”

“The whole atmosphere,” I said. “Did you notice the staff at the park gates?”

He chuckled. “Them? What’s wrong with them? Aside from looking like they’re full of resentment while saying the most dreamy lines. Honestly, they remind me of myself at work—smiling through the grind. Ha!”

His laugh rang out, casual and dismissive, cutting through my unease.

Murder False / Ending +0 
I let the thought slip away, deciding not to dwell on it any further. The music and chatter swallowed my doubts, and for the moment, I convinced myself everything was fine.
[[Next->page 8]]
(display:"Styles")


:: Response [en] {"position":"475,250","size":"100,100"}
"Hey are u fine? Get up first,” I said, his voice edged with unease. I was confused and ask him more “What did you mean by those words just now?”

The vagrant’s eyes flickered with something between fear and warning. “The rules… they’re real. Don’t break them.”

With that, he spun on his heel and bolted into the shadows, leaving only the echo of his words hanging in the air.

(set: $sanity to it - 70)
