:: Tell him about the strange atmosphere [en] {"position":"975,225","size":"100,100"}
I forced a smile. 

“I’m fine,” 

Samuel tilted his head, studying me. 

“You’re sure? Don’t tell me that homeless guy spooked you.”

“Maybe I’m just not feeling well today,” I muttered

He gave a small shrug, apparently satisfied, and turned his attention back to the crowd. The music swelled, the crimson tent loomed larger, and the line pressed forward.

But inside, my pulse wouldn’t settle. His casual dismissal only deepened the chill in my chest. The word from the brochure echoed again in my mind—dealt with.

Samuel didn’t notice. He was already caught up in the excitement, while I was left alone with the gnawing suspicion that I had just stepped into the wrong story, one that might not let me walk back out.

Ending‑1: Murder True 
The choice to stay silent sealed my fate.
[[Next->page 8]]
(display:"Styles")


:: page 1 [en] {"position":"225,300","size":"100,100"}
As dusk approached and the "Monster Project" began, I entered the park and walked through a long corridor adorned with flags.

Beside the corridor was a vast parking lot, darkened for some reason, adding an eerie ambiance to the bustling park.
 
[[Next->page 2]]
(display:"Styles")


:: page 10 [en] {"position":"1350,300","size":"100,100"}
BOOM!

All in a sudden, the lights snapped off.

No warning, no flicker, just sudden, absolute darkness, as though someone had yanked the power cord from the entire tent.

Four or five hundred people froze, their voices rising in confusion. Children began to cry, their wails piercing the black. Adults cursed, muttered, some tried to stand, others pushed toward the exits. The air was thick with panic, the kind that spreads fast when no one knows what’s happening.

It was pure chaos. The darkness felt endless, pressing in from every side. Just when the crowd’s unease was about to boil over, a voice cut through the chaos—calm, theatrical, chilling.


A spotlight shone towards the middle of the stage, the host stood there and picked up his mic, “Let the show… begin!”

[[Next->page 11]]
(display:"Styles")


:: page 11 [en] {"position":"1475,300","size":"100,100"}



